\title{Dnanexus Integration}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"DNAnexus cloud genomics platform. Build apps/applets, manage data (upload/download), dxpy Python SDK, run workflows, FASTQ/BAM/VCF, for genomics pipeline development and execution."}

\subtree{
\title{DNAnexus Integration}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{DNAnexus is a cloud platform for biomedical data analysis and genomics. Build and deploy apps/applets, manage data objects, run workflows, and use the dxpy Python SDK for genomics pipeline development and execution.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when:}

\ul{
\li{Creating, building, or modifying DNAnexus apps/applets}
\li{Uploading, downloading, searching, or organizing files and records}
\li{Running analyses, monitoring jobs, creating workflows}
\li{Writing scripts using dxpy to interact with the platform}
\li{Setting up dxapp.json, managing dependencies, using Docker}
\li{Processing FASTQ, BAM, VCF, or other bioinformatics files}
\li{Managing projects, permissions, or platform resources}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\p{The skill is organized into five main areas, each with detailed reference documentation:}

\subtree{
\title{1. App Development}
\p{\strong{Purpose}: Create executable programs (apps/applets) that run on the DNAnexus platform.}

\p{\strong{Key Operations}:}

\ul{
\li{Generate app skeleton with \code{\startverb dx-app-wizard\stopverb}}
\li{Write Python or Bash apps with proper entry points}
\li{Handle input/output data objects}
\li{Deploy with \code{\startverb dx build\stopverb} or \code{\startverb dx build --app\stopverb}}
\li{Test apps on the platform}
}

\p{\strong{Common Use Cases}:}

\ul{
\li{Bioinformatics pipelines (alignment, variant calling)}
\li{Data processing workflows}
\li{Quality control and filtering}
\li{Format conversion tools}
}

\p{\strong{Reference}: See \code{\startverb references/app-development.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Complete app structure and patterns}
\li{Python entry point decorators}
\li{Input/output handling with dxpy}
\li{Development best practices}
\li{Common issues and solutions}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Data Operations}
\p{\strong{Purpose}: Manage files, records, and other data objects on the platform.}

\p{\strong{Key Operations}:}

\ul{
\li{Upload/download files with \code{\startverb dxpy.upload_local_file()\stopverb} and \code{\startverb dxpy.download_dxfile()\stopverb}}
\li{Create and manage records with metadata}
\li{Search for data objects by name, properties, or type}
\li{Clone data between projects}
\li{Manage project folders and permissions}
}

\p{\strong{Common Use Cases}:}

\ul{
\li{Uploading sequencing data (FASTQ files)}
\li{Organizing analysis results}
\li{Searching for specific samples or experiments}
\li{Backing up data across projects}
\li{Managing reference genomes and annotations}
}

\p{\strong{Reference}: See \code{\startverb references/data-operations.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Complete file and record operations}
\li{Data object lifecycle (open/closed states)}
\li{Search and discovery patterns}
\li{Project management}
\li{Batch operations}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Job Execution}
\p{\strong{Purpose}: Run analyses, monitor execution, and orchestrate workflows.}

\p{\strong{Key Operations}:}

\ul{
\li{Launch jobs with \code{\startverb applet.run()\stopverb} or \code{\startverb app.run()\stopverb}}
\li{Monitor job status and logs}
\li{Create subjobs for parallel processing}
\li{Build and run multi-step workflows}
\li{Chain jobs with output references}
}

\p{\strong{Common Use Cases}:}

\ul{
\li{Running genomics analyses on sequencing data}
\li{Parallel processing of multiple samples}
\li{Multi-step analysis pipelines}
\li{Monitoring long-running computations}
\li{Debugging failed jobs}
}

\p{\strong{Reference}: See \code{\startverb references/job-execution.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Complete job lifecycle and states}
\li{Workflow creation and orchestration}
\li{Parallel execution patterns}
\li{Job monitoring and debugging}
\li{Resource management}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Python SDK (dxpy)}
\p{\strong{Purpose}: Programmatic access to DNAnexus platform through Python.}

\p{\strong{Key Operations}:}

\ul{
\li{Work with data object handlers (DXFile, DXRecord, DXApplet, etc.)}
\li{Use high-level functions for common tasks}
\li{Make direct API calls for advanced operations}
\li{Create links and references between objects}
\li{Search and discover platform resources}
}

\p{\strong{Common Use Cases}:}

\ul{
\li{Automation scripts for data management}
\li{Custom analysis pipelines}
\li{Batch processing workflows}
\li{Integration with external tools}
\li{Data migration and organization}
}

\p{\strong{Reference}: See \code{\startverb references/python-sdk.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Complete dxpy class reference}
\li{High-level utility functions}
\li{API method documentation}
\li{Error handling patterns}
\li{Common code patterns}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Configuration and Dependencies}
\p{\strong{Purpose}: Configure app metadata and manage dependencies.}

\p{\strong{Key Operations}:}

\ul{
\li{Write dxapp.json with inputs, outputs, and run specs}
\li{Install system packages (execDepends)}
\li{Bundle custom tools and resources}
\li{Use assets for shared dependencies}
\li{Integrate Docker containers}
\li{Configure instance types and timeouts}
}

\p{\strong{Common Use Cases}:}

\ul{
\li{Defining app input/output specifications}
\li{Installing bioinformatics tools (samtools, bwa, etc.)}
\li{Managing Python package dependencies}
\li{Using Docker images for complex environments}
\li{Selecting computational resources}
}

\p{\strong{Reference}: See \code{\startverb references/configuration.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Complete dxapp.json specification}
\li{Dependency management strategies}
\li{Docker integration patterns}
